---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="caring for your keychains">
  <article class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">
    <a href="/blog" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-primary transition-colors market-aware-link" data-href="/blog">← back to blog</a>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-6 mb-2">May 18, 2026</p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-6">how to care for your acrylic keychains</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-sm text-gray-600 space-y-4 leading-relaxed">
      <p>acrylic keychains are made to travel with you — on your bag, keys, or phone strap. a little care goes a long way in keeping them cute for years.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-800 pt-2">avoid sharp impacts</h2>
      <p>acrylic can scratch if tossed into a bag with keys and coins. use a small pouch or clip it to the outside of your bag where it won't rub against hard objects.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-800 pt-2">clean gently</h2>
      <p>wipe with a soft, slightly damp microfiber cloth. avoid alcohol-based cleaners that can dull printed surfaces over time.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-800 pt-2">keep away from extreme heat</h2>
      <p>don't leave keychains in a hot car or direct sunlight for long periods. heat can soften acrylic and affect the print.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-800 pt-2">check the hardware</h2>
      <p>every few months, make sure the jump ring and clasp are snug. a quick tighten prevents accidental drops.</p>

      <p class="pt-4">treat your keychain like a tiny art piece — because it is. explore more designs in our <a href="/products" class="text-primary hover:underline market-aware-link" data-href="/products">keychain collection</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
